[y,0] \implies \exists \zeta \in (y, 0)
\begin{align}          &g(0) - g(y) = g'(\zeta)(0 - y) = (1 + c f'(\zeta)) |y| \ge (1 - ck) |y|\\ \implies &g(y) \le g(0) - (1-ck) |y| \end{align}
g(y)
